# Radio

`TxRadioGroup` coordinates a set of `TxRadio` items for one primitive `string | number` value. Use the button style for compact segmented choices, the standard style for familiar form rows, and the card style when each option needs supporting copy.

## Standard Single-Select

Standard radios render a dot indicator and label. `direction="row"` keeps short choices compact, while column direction remains available for longer lists.

### Radio (standard)
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="RadioRadioStandardDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import type { TxRadioValue } from '@talex-touch/tuffex'
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const value = ref<TxRadioValue>('editor')
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxRadioGroup v-model="value" type="standard" direction="row">
      <TxRadio value="viewer" label="Viewer" />
      <TxRadio value="editor" label="Editor" />
      <TxRadio value="owner" label="Owner" />
    </TxRadioGroup>
  </template>
---
:::

## Card Single-Select

Card radios use the default slot for richer option content. Disabled cards stay visible, cannot be selected, and are skipped by keyboard navigation.

