## Interaction Contract

- `TxRadioGroup` owns the selected primitive value and provides type, disabled state, and keyboard navigation to child radios.
- Clicking an enabled unchecked `TxRadio` emits `click` on that item and `update:modelValue` / `change` from the group.
- Clicking the already checked radio is a no-op; radio groups are single-choice by design.
- Group-level `disabled` disables every child. Item-level `disabled` disables only that radio.
- Keyboard navigation uses only enabled radios: arrow keys wrap, and `Home` / `End` jump to the first / last enabled item.
- Button groups render an animated indicator. For `glass` and `blur` indicators, `updateOnSettled` defaults to waiting for the indicator to settle before emitting the model update.
- `direction` only affects `standard` and `card` groups. Button groups always resolve to row layout.

## API

### TxRadioGroup Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `modelValue` / `v-model` | `string \| number` | - | Selected radio value. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables all radios in the group and blocks keyboard selection. |
| `type` | `'button' \| 'standard' \| 'card'` | `'button'` | Visual style shared by child radios. |
| `direction` | `'row' \| 'column'` | - | Layout direction. `button` always resolves to row, `standard` defaults to row, and `card` defaults to column. |
| `indicatorVariant` | `'solid' \| 'outline' \| 'glass' \| 'blur'` | - | Button-group indicator style. When omitted, `glass` maps to `glass`, `blur` maps to `blur`, otherwise `solid` is used. |
| `glass` | `boolean` | `false` | Shortcut for the `glass` button indicator variant. |
| `blur` | `boolean` | `false` | Shortcut for the `blur` button indicator variant. |
| `updateOnSettled` | `boolean` | - | For button groups, delays v-model/change emission until the animated indicator settles. Defaults to enabled for `glass` or `blur` indicators. |
| `stiffness` | `number` | `110` | Spring stiffness for button indicator motion. Higher values settle faster. |
| `damping` | `number` | `12` | Spring damping for button indicator motion. Lower values feel more elastic. |
| `blurAmount` | `number` | `1` | Backdrop blur strength for the `blur` indicator. |
| `elastic` | `boolean` | `true` | Enables stretch/impact motion on the button indicator. |

### TxRadioGroup Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `update:modelValue` | `(value: string \| number)` | Emitted when an enabled child radio selects a new value. |
| `change` | `(value: string \| number)` | Emitted with the selected value after an enabled selection. |

### Keyboard

| Key | Behavior |
|------|------|
| `ArrowRight` / `ArrowDown` | Select the next enabled radio. |
| `ArrowLeft` / `ArrowUp` | Select the previous enabled radio. |
| `Home` / `End` | Select the first / last enabled radio. |

### TxRadio Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|------|
| `value` | `string \| number` | - | Value written to the parent `TxRadioGroup` when selected. |
| `label` | `string` | `''` | Fallback visible label when no default slot is provided. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disables this radio and removes it from group keyboard navigation. |
| `type` | `'button' \| 'standard' \| 'card'` | `'button'` | Standalone visual style when the radio is not controlled by a group; grouped radios inherit the group type. |

### TxRadio Events

| Event | Params | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `click` | `(value: string \| number)` | Emitted after an enabled, unchecked radio selects itself through the parent group. |

## Slots

### TxRadioGroup

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| `default` | - | Place `TxRadio` children here. The group provides selected value, disabled state, and visual type through injection. |

### TxRadio

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| `default` | - | Visible label or rich card content. Falls back to the `label` prop when omitted. |

## Best Practices

- Keep every `TxRadio.value` unique within a group; duplicate primitives make checked state ambiguous.
- Use `label` for simple text-only radios and the default slot for card content or formatted labels.
- Prefer `type="standard" direction="column"` for long form choices, `type="button"` for short segmented controls, and `type="card"` when each option needs explanatory copy.
- For `glass` / `blur` indicators, keep `updateOnSettled` default unless form validation must run immediately. The default waits for motion to settle before emitting.
- Disable unavailable options individually so users can see why a choice exists but is not selectable; disable the group only for read-only or loading states.
- Do not rely on `direction` for button groups. Button radios always resolve to row layout.

